Android Development (Java) Quiz
Question 1
Which method is the first to be called when an Activity is created?
	• A) onStart()
	• B) onCreate()
	• C) onResume()
	• D) onInitialize()
	• Correct Answer: B
Question 2
Which class is used to navigate from one Activity to another?
	• A) Link
	• B) Switcher
	• C) Intent
	• D) Navigator
	• Correct Answer: C
Question 3
Where is the app's package name and permissions declared?
	• A) MainActivity.java
	• B) AndroidManifest.xml
	• C) build.gradle
	• D) strings.xml
	• Correct Answer: B
Question 4
What is used to display a small, temporary message on the screen?
	• A) Log.d()
	• B) Alert()
	• C) Toast
	• D) Notify()
	• Correct Answer: C
Question 5
Which interface is used to handle a button click in Java?
	• A) OnClickListener
	• B) OnTouchListener
	• C) OnHoldListener
	• D) ActionListener
	• Correct Answer: A
Question 6
Which keyword is used to inherit properties from one class to another?
	• A) implements
	• B) includes
	• C) extends
	• D) inherits
	• Correct Answer: C
Question 7
In which file are external library dependencies (implementation) added?
	• A) settings.gradle
	• B) build.gradle (Module level)
	• C) AndroidManifest.xml
	• D) config.xml
	• Correct Answer: B
Question 8
What is the purpose of findViewById()?
	• A) To create a new screen
	• B) To link an XML view to a Java object
	• C) To search for data in the database
	• D) To connect the app to the internet
	• Correct Answer: B
Question 9
Which keyword makes a variable's value constant (cannot be changed)?
	• A) static
	• B) final
	• C) constant
	• D) fixed
	• Correct Answer: B
Question 10
Which view is the most memory-efficient for displaying long lists?
	• A) ScrollView
	• B) ListView
	• C) RecyclerView
	• D) TableLayout
	• Correct Answer: C
